            <div>
                <head>About this document</head>
                <p>
                    This document proposes the addition of a TEI module for correspondence. 
                    It is the product of a Correspondence SIG task force (Sabine Seifert, Marcel Illetschko, Peter Stadler) 
                    with valuable input from various people.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The aim of the proposal is to define a common set of correspondence specific meta data,
                    brought together at one place in the TEI header.
                    
                    The lack of special Guidelines for encoding letters, postcards, etc. with TEI P5
                    has been a recurring topic since the formation of the Correspondence SIG in 2008.
                    Additionally, there is a growing demand of correspondence projects for linked data facilities.
                    
                    For this, we suggest two encoding approaches within this set:
                    <list type="simple">
                        <item>an elaborate structure for detailed data capture,</item>
                        <item>a basic structure for easy data interchange.</item>
                    </list>
                    
                    A guiding idea has been to only tentatively modify the TEI standard by adding just a few elements, 
                    wrapping them in a special purpose element <gi>ct:correspDesc</gi> and injecting the latter into <gi>sourceDesc</gi>.
                    
                    This is supposed to be just a first step in the Correspondence SIG's strive for a complete model of encoding correspondence material.
                    
                    <!--While some of this information can already be encoded in various sections of the TEI header we believe it to be of greater value 
                    for projects dealing with correspondence material to have this information in one place.-->
                    
                </p>
                
                <div>
                    <head>Conventions used</head>
                    <p>
                        As required for TEI conformance, non-TEI elements are defined in a distinct non-TEI namespace. 
                        In the usage examples and throughout this document that namespace is mapped to the prefix <hi rend="bold">ct:</hi> (= correspondence taskforce), 
                        while TEI elements are not marked by any namespace prefix.
                    </p>
                </div>
                
            </div>
